        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32311",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thing2b",
                        "name": "thing2b",
                        "displayName": "thing2b",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This could also help replace the getMimeType() method on Zend_Service_Amazon_S3, which converts file extensions to mime types. ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thing2b",
                        "name": "thing2b",
                        "displayName": "thing2b",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-06-30T19:15:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-06-30T19:15:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32315",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "There's a great list of file extensions and mime types in one of the apache config files: http:\/\/svn.apache.org\/viewvc\/httpd\/httpd\/trunk\/docs\/conf\/mime.types Maybe we could use that one.The last comment says it's in the public domain.\n\nBeside finfo (which is part of PHP 5.3 IIRC) we can also use getimagesize().\n\nI see how I get time to write a little guesser class. But I don't have a problem if anyone else is quicker ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=nico",
                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-01T04:11:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-01T04:11:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/35947",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It seems to be also one of issues for next major release like as ZF-1490 . Do you have any idea ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-11T21:48:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-11T21:48:19.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36550",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I will note on here  http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/wiki\/display\/ZFDEV2\/Mail+sending+and+building+enhancements+2.0",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-11-28T06:27:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-11-28T06:27:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36718",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "IMO, it seems to be better that we would submit a new proposal.\r\nBecause I think this issue might be new feature rather than expansion of existing Zend_Mime.\r\n\r\nI expect the class name with Zend_Filter_File_MimeType as one of converters about file's infomation, or Zend_Mime_Type as specialty handler of Mime types.\r\n\r\nThe class might have 2 kinds method.\r\n\r\n1)\r\nSimple converter from file's extension to MIME type. for example, getTypeByExtension().\r\nit may be required for getMimeType() of Zend_Service_Amazon_S3 (mentioned by thing2b).\r\n\r\n2) Information extracter from file with finfo() or getimagesize(). For example, getTypeByFinfo().\r\nOr we might substitute it by getMimeType() of Zend_File_Transfer_Adapter\r\n\r\nI hope it could help you ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-04T21:45:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-04T21:56:05.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36724",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Note that Zend_Filter is not the correct component for getting the mimetype of an file.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-05T01:50:32.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-05T01:50:32.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36725",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Detaching Zend_Filter",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-05T01:50:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-05T01:50:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36726",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Note that finfo is availalble also to 5.2.4 installations.\r\n\r\nZend_Mime was designed ONLY for usage with Zend_Mail.\r\nTherefor it is not used in other places of the framework.\r\n\r\nNote that Zend_File_Transfer is ONLY for usage while transferring a file, and not for existing files somewhere in a directory. When you let file-transfer detect the mime type based on the extension as proposed abbove it's a VERY HUGE security risk.\r\n\r\nThe base question is, if we want to couple two components more together for a functionallity which is available within vanilla PHP installations. I would say no.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thomas",
                        "name": "thomas",
                        "displayName": "Thomas Weidner",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-05T01:57:44.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-05T01:57:44.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36737",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thing2b",
                        "name": "thing2b",
                        "displayName": "thing2b",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "You say that \"Zend_Mime was designed ONLY for usage with Zend_Mail.\"\r\nIf this is the case, why was Zend_Mime not called Zend_Mail_Mime?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=thing2b",
                        "name": "thing2b",
                        "displayName": "thing2b",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-05T14:32:47.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-05T14:32:47.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36748",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank You opinions, Thomas and thing2b .\r\n\r\nI will be happy if reporter or participants would submit proposal.\r\nBecause the MIME type *database* seems to be independent with the existing Zend_Mime functions and also Zend_Mail one.\r\n\r\nRather, it is required with other components.\r\nIt would be better to ask review for many reviewers about the database .\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=satoruyoshida",
                        "name": "satoruyoshida",
                        "displayName": "Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-06T04:17:40.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-06T04:17:40.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/36760",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "body": "I don't see why Zend_Mime can't be used whenever we need to do something with MIME. What in Zend_Mime prevents us from using it anywhere we want to?\r\n\r\nBTW, having good list of MIME types for files can help mailing too, if you are mailing files. But doesn't have to be for mail exclusively.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stas",
                        "name": "stas",
                        "displayName": "Stanislav Malyshev",
                        "active": false
                    },
                    "created": "2009-12-07T00:16:33.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-12-07T00:17:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/44024",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mayhem",
                        "name": "mayhem",
                        "displayName": "mayhem",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "So what the results of this talking? I'm also interested to have tools to work with mime, and as we all can see this tools implemented in wide range of components, and all this components has its own realisation.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mayhem",
                        "name": "mayhem",
                        "displayName": "mayhem",
                        "active": true
